{{Infobox historic building | name = Isfahan Museum of Contemporary Art | native_name = موزه هنرهای معاصر اصفهان | native_name_lang = fa | former_names = | alternate_names = | status = Cultural | image = Isfahan Museum of Contemporary Art.jpg | image_alt = | caption = | map_type = Iran | map_alt = | map_caption = Location within [[Iran]] | embedded = | altitude = | building_type = [[Museum]] | architectural_style = [[Isfahani style|Isfahani]] | structural_system = | cost = | client = | owner = [[Cultural Heritage, Handcrafts and Tourism Organization]] | current_tenants = | landlord = | location = [[Isfahan]], [[Iran]] | address = | coordinates = {{coord|32.6580|51.6741|region:IR|display=inline,title}} | groundbreaking_date = | start_date = | completion_date = | completed_date = | opened_date = | height = | floor_count = | floor_area = | url = | references = }}
The '''Isfahan Museum of Contemporary Art''' (aka the '''Museum of Contemporary Art'''<ref>{{cite web| title=Museum of Contemporary Art | url=http://www.lonelyplanet.com/iran/central-iran/esfahan/sights/museums-galleries/museum-contemporary-art |publisher=[[Lonely Planet]] | accessdate=7 June 2014 }}</ref>) is a [[contemporary art]] museum in [[Isfahan]], [[Iran]], located next to the Museum of Natural History.<ref>{{cite web| title=Museum of Contemporary Art | url=http://www.irhal.com/Iran/Isfahan/Places-To-Visit/Museum-of-Contemporary-Art.html |website=www.irhal.com| accessdate=7 June 2014 }}</ref>
==Building== The museum building dates from the [[Safavid]] era. Many changes were made to the building during the [[Qajar]] era. The building has been decorated by [[stucco]]ed forms, which are the principal architectural feature of the Qajar period. There are many patterns of flowers and vase, which are a distinctive feature of decoration in the Qajar period. This feature is one that distinguishes the Qajar age from the Safavid age, in which flowers were never in vases.<ref name="Rāhnamā 2004, p. 137">{{cite book| title=Rāhnamā ye Safar be Ostān e Esfāhān (Travel Guide for the Province Isfahan) | publisher=Rouzane | isbn=964-334-218-2 | first=Hosseyn | last=Yaghoubi | editor-first=Arash | editor-last=Beheshti | page=137 | language=Persian | year=2004 }}</ref>
==Museum== The [[museum]] is open from 9 a.m. to 12 p.m. and from 5 to 8 p.m. in the spring and summer. In the autumn and winter, it is open from 9 a.m. to 12 p.m. and 4 to 7 p.m.<ref name="Rāhnamā 2004, p. 137"/>
